to the editor re at fox news the colonel who was n't business day april 29 there have been many executives who pad their resumes but only the more flamboyant ones make the news as president of an executive search firm for more than two decades i have lost track of all the pretenders we have uncovered most major companies have more than just a few on the payroll unfortunately human nature mitigates against the unmasking of charlatans by hiring managers the most proficient charlatans are charismatic to a fault by the time a senior executive is ready to make an employment offer he or she is blinded to the subtle signs that all is not as it appears we always caution our clients that background and reference checks should never be totally performed by the hiring superior who can rarely be objective stanley herz somers ny april 29 2002

